ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Calculate number of subnets inside the enterprise network?

Host X has IP address 192.168.1.97 and is connected through two routers R1 and R2 to another host Y with IP address 192.168.1.80. Router R1 has IP address 192.168.1.135 and 192.168.1.110. R2 has IP address 192.168.1.67 and 192.168.1.155. The network mask used in network 255.255.255.224. Given information above, how many distinct subnets are guaranteed to already exist in network?

Consider three machines M, N and P with IP addresses 100.10.5.2, 100.10.5.5 and 100.10.5.6 respectively. The subnet mask is set to 255.255.255.252 for all the three machines. Which one of following is true?
ENGLISH.OPT1: M, N and P all belong to same subnet
ENGLISH.OPT2: Only M and N belong to same subnet
ENGLISH.OPT3: Only N and P belong to same subnet
ENGLISH.OPT4: M, N and P belong to different subnets

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Calculate number of collision domains and broadcast domains?
In the below diagram source S is connected to destination D via the mediating router R. How many times transport TCP headers are attached and removed?
Present sender window size in slow start algorithm of TCP is 6400 bytes. Maximum segment size is 200 bytes. What would be the next window size in (mss) if no congestion happens ? _______
Calculate the number of times TCP checksum is calculated from S to D when data is transmitted from S to D?
Which of following is true in case of networking protocols?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Segmentation is done when transport layer is giving data to network layer.
ENGLISH.OPT2: Fragmentation is done when network layer is giving data to data link layer.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Which of following is true with respect to port number and protocol field of transport protocol and IP protocol?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Application layer protocols like HTTP, DNS, SMTP, FTP can be identified and distinguished by protocol field of IP protocol.
ENGLISH.OPT2: Application layer protocols like HTTP, DNS, SMTP, FTP can be identified and distinguished by port address of transport layer.
ENGLISH.OPT3: Transport layer protocols like TCP, UDP and Network layer protocol like IP, ICMP, RARP can be distinguished by protocol field of IP protocol.
ENGLISH.OPT4: Transport layer protocols like TCP, UDP and Network layer protocol like IP, ICMP, RARP can be distinguished by port number of transport layer.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: The correct order of calculations at sender side while transmitting data to receiver in network?
ENGLISH.OPT1: TCP checksum for segment, CRC calculation for frame, IP header calculation.
ENGLISH.OPT2: TCP checksum for segment, IP header calculation, CRC calculation for frame.
ENGLISH.OPT3: CRC calculation for frame, IP header calculation, TCP checksum for segment.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Which of following is true in case of network protocols?
ENGLISH.OPT1: The sequence number of segment is (100 –199). So it is SYN segment.
ENGLISH.OPT2: The sequence number of segment is m the sequence number of subsequent segment must be m + 1.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Which sequence number is not possible for a byte in a TCP protocol?

ENGLISH.OPT2: HLEN bits of 0100 in IP protocol is a valid possibility.
ENGLISH.OPT3: TTL value will change for packets at every hop from end to end in internet.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT:
Consider an IP packet with a length of 4500 bytes that includes 20 byte IPv4 header and 40 bytes TCP header. The packet is forwarded to an IPv4 router that supports a MTU of 600 bytes. Assume that the length of IP header in all the outgoing fragments of this packet is 20 bytes. Assume that the fragmentation offset stored in first fragment is 0.
The fragmentation offset stored in third fragment is ________.

Given window size parameter of TCP header is given as 1111111111111110.
No window scaling factor is applied in options and padding. Calculate the segment size of TCP ________ bytes.
Which of following is correct with respect to transport protocol?
ENGLISH.OPT1: In slow start algorithm of TCP, the increase of sender window size is based on ACK.
ENGLISH.OPT2: UDP protocol is connection oriented virtually at destination with help of sequence number.
ENGLISH.OPT3: Purpose of persistence timer is to overcome deadlock between client and server processes in network.
ENGLISH.OPT4: UDP is unreliable and supports broadcasting.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT:
Consider two hosts P and Q connected through a router R, the Maximum Transfer Unit (MTU) value of link between P and r is 1500 bytes and between R and Q is 820 bytes. A TCP segment of size 1400 bytes was transferred from P to Q through R with IP identification value as 0x1234. Assume that the IP header size is 20 bytes. Further, the packet is allowed to be fragmented i.e. don’t fragment (DF) flag in IP header is not set by P.
Which of following statements is/are correct?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Two fragments are created at R and IP datagram size carrying second fragment is 620 bytes.
ENGLISH.OPT2: If the second fragment is lost, R will resend fragment with IP identification value 0x1234.
ENGLISH.OPT3: If the second fragment is lost, P is required to resend the whole TCP segment.
ENGLISH.OPT4: TCP destination port can be determined by analysing only second fragment.
